<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">

  <!-- SEO Optimization -->
  <title>Word Counter Tool - Count Words, Characters, and Lines</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Quickly count words, characters, and lines in your text with our free online word counter.  A simple tool for writers, students, and developers.">
  <meta name="keywords" content="word count, word counter, character count, line count, text analysis, text tool, online word counter, word counter tool, character counter, line counter">
  <meta name="author" content="SOFTICA">

  <!-- Open Graph -->
  <meta property="og:title" content="Word Counter Tool">
  <meta property="og:description" content="Count words, characters, and lines in your text with this free online tool.">
  <meta property="og:type" content="website">
  <meta property="og:url" content="https://util-tool-online.com/word-counter"> <!-- Update with your actual URL -->
  <meta property="og:image" content="https://util-tool-online.com/images/util-tool-online.png"> <!-- Update with your image URL -->

  <!-- Twitter Cards -->
  <meta name="twitter:card" content="https://util-tool-online.com/images/util-tool-online.png">
  <meta name="twitter:title" content="Word Counter Tool">
  <meta name="twitter:description" content="Easily count words, characters, and lines in your text.">
  <meta name="twitter:image" content="https://util-tool-online.com/images/util-tool-online.png"> <!-- Update with your image URL -->

  <!-- Styles -->
  <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css">
</head>
<body>
  <%- include('partials/header') %>

  <div class="container mt-5">
    <div class="row">
      <!-- Left Menu -->
      <div class="col-md-2">
        <%- include('partials/left-menu') %>
      </div>

      <!-- Main Content -->
      <div class="col-md-10">
        <h1>Word Counter Tool</h1>
        <p>This tool helps you quickly count the number of words, characters (with and without spaces), and lines in your text.</p>

        <!-- Usage Instructions -->
        <section class="mt-4">
          <h2>How to Use</h2>
          <ol>
            <li>Paste your text into the input box below.</li>
            <li>Click the "Count" button.</li>
            <li>The results will be displayed below.</li>
            <li>Click "Clear" to reset.</li>
          </ol>
        </section>

        <!-- Input Section -->
        <section class="mt-5">
          <h2>Enter Text</h2>
          <form id="word-counter-form" action="/word-counter" method="POST">
            <div class="mb-3">
              <label for="text" class="form-label">Enter Text</label>
              <textarea class="form-control" id="text" name="text" rows="6" required><%= text || '' %></textarea>
            </div>
            <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Count</button>
            <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" id="clear-btn">Clear</button>
          </form>
        </section>

        <!-- Result Section -->
        <% if (charCount !== null) { %>
        <section class="mt-5">
          <h2>Results</h2>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Total Characters:</strong> <%= charCount %></li>
            <li><strong>Characters (without spaces):</strong> <%= withoutSpacesCount %></li>
            <li><strong>Words:</strong> <%= wordCount %></li>
            <li><strong>Lines:</strong> <%= lineCount %></li>
          </ul>
        </section>
        <% } %>

        <!-- About Word Counter Section -->
        <section class="mt-5">
          <h2>About This Word Counter</h2>
          <p>A word counter is a tool used to determine the number of words, characters, and lines within a given text.  It's useful for:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Writing and Editing:</strong> Meeting word count requirements for essays, articles, etc.</li>
            <li><strong>SEO:</strong> Analyzing text length for search engine optimization.</li>
            <li><strong>Data Analysis:</strong> Getting quick statistics about text data.</li>
            <li><strong>Software Development:</strong> Counting code lines or characters.</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Advantages</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Speed and Efficiency: Quickly obtain text statistics.</li>
            <li>Accuracy: Provides precise counts.</li>
            <li>Simplicity: Easy to use.</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Disadvantages</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Limited Analysis:  Provides only basic text statistics; doesn't offer deeper linguistic analysis.</li>
            <li>Context-Dependent: Word counting can be affected by punctuation and formatting.</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Examples</h3>
          <p><strong>Example 1:</strong></p>
          <p>Input: "This is a sentence." Output: Total Characters: 18, Characters (without spaces): 14, Words: 4, Lines: 1</p>
          <p><strong>Example 2:</strong></p>
          <p>Input: "This is a longer text with multiple lines.\nThis is the second line."</p>
          <p>Output:  Total Characters: 66, Characters (without spaces): 54, Words: 14, Lines: 2</p>
        </section>

        <!-- Clear Button Script -->
        <script>
          document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
            const clearBtn = document.getElementById('clear-btn');
            const textArea = document.getElementById('text');

            clearBtn?.addEventListener('click', () => {
              textArea.value = '';
            });
          });
        </script>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <%- include('partials/footer') %>
</body>
</html>
